This is an entry to mid level role at our Australian company working
nationally and internationally. We are looking for the right people to join
our team who can assist our clients improve their Information Security posture
and grow further into a leadership role.

Candidates would generally have 3 years experience in MSP or service desk with
a keen interest for a security and GRC focussed career. The successful
candidate will likely be undertaking or have completed courses such as CISPP
and been involved in tasks specifically to security such as responding and
writing incident reports or managing security products such as firewalls.
Knowledge and having worked within ISO 27001 certified environments will also
be of benefit.

** What a normal day looks like for you in this role: **

  * Consult with our technical teams on security baselines 
  * Perform threat response and actions 
  * Manage security training systems 
  * Assist with our internal GRC requirements 
  * Undertake security assessments with our clients of varying sizes 
  * Contribute to the design and delivery of projects 
  * Be involved in client workshops 

This is a great opportunity to join our highly skilled team. If you are
looking for a new challenge then please apply now.

